verbose_text: Initial laboratory results revealed that older patients had lower hemoglobin [122.1 (+/-16.4) vs 135.0 (+/-19.4), p = 0.002] and albumin [38.0 (+/-47) vs 41.4 (+/-4.1), p < 0.001] and higher urea level [7.9 (5.8-12.4) vs 5.8 (4.8-8.4), p = 0.011] compared to their younger counterparts.
